  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 676 (as3436): __le__, __gt__, __ge__ dict-presence checks for asyncio types."
    - "Theme: __le__/__gt__/__ge__ dict-presence (x<=y, x>y, x>=y)."
    - "All values False — these types do not define ordering comparison operators in their own __dict__."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: asyncio.Task, asyncio.Future, asyncio.Event, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.Queue, asyncio.PriorityQueue, asyncio.LifoQueue."
    - "Key finding (__le__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __le__. <= delegates to __le__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. asyncio types do not define __le__ in their own __dict__ — the <= operator is not part of the public API for any asyncio synchronization primitive, task, or queue type. asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles with no custom __le__ in their own __dict__. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: boolean-state and permit-count guards with no __le__ defined at the class level. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __le__ in their own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__gt__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __gt__. > delegates to __gt__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. asyncio types do not define __gt__ in their own __dict__; no greater-than comparison is supported for these types. asyncio.Task/Future: these types have distinct identities per coroutine and loop; no ordering is defined in their own __dict__. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization guards with no __gt__ defined in their own __dict__. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __gt__ in their own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__ge__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __ge__. >= delegates to __ge__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. asyncio types define no ordering protocol in their own __dict__. asyncio.PriorityQueue sorts its items, but the queue itself has no __ge__ in its __dict__ — comparison applies to the items stored, not the queue object. asyncio.Task/Future/Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore/Queue/LifoQueue: none define __ge__ in their own __dict__."
    - "Continues the all-false run from wave 656 (__call__/__len__/__getitem__) through wave 676 (__le__/__gt__/__ge__) — twenty-one consecutive waves of 100% false results for asyncio types."
    - "Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:"
    - "  Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 660 (as3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 661 (as3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 662 (as3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 663 (as3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 664 (as3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 665 (as3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 666 (as3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 667 (as3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 10."
