# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __le__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__le__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __le__.
# <= delegates to __le__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# asyncio types do not define __le__ in their own __dict__; the <=
#   operator is not part of the public API for any asyncio type.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles with no custom __le__
#   in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state synchronization guards with
#   no __le__ in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-count guards with no __le__
#   defined at the class level in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __le__ in
#   their own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

