# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __gt__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__gt__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __gt__.
# > delegates to __gt__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# asyncio types do not define __gt__ in their own __dict__; greater-than
#   comparison is not part of the public API for any asyncio type.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles compared by identity, not
#   value; no __gt__ defined in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: synchronization guards with no __gt__
#   in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-count guards with no __gt__
#   defined at the class level in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __gt__ in
#   their own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

